  RELEVANCE: Murphy's cooperative principle provides the strongest theoretical foundation for percentage-based giving norms. If fair shares can be calculated as percentages of income (or wealth), then 10% pledges represent not arbitrary stopping points but principled distributions of the collective burden. This directly supports income-based over purely asset-based norms, as fair shares are naturally calculated from flows rather than stocks.

